        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39872",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think that you misunderstood what time synchronisation should do.\r\n\r\nUsing timesync you say that Zend_Date MUST return the actual date. Regardless of any given input.\r\n\r\nThere is, and there must be no way to change the time and date which is returned by the timeserver.\r\n\r\nWhen you need to change the result which is returned by the timeserver then you must do this after object creation.\r\n\r\nThe default offset is set by Zend_TimeSync... there are just two ways how time synchronisation can be used. Directly or by using the option timesync. But from handling they are both more or less equal.",
